        "timestamp": 1751097900
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>No. Note that the equality you've written wouldn't normally typecheck, and the only reason it does here is because <code>Univ</code> is actually a family of constants and you've asserted that <code>Univ.{u} ≍ univ.{u+1}</code>. So actually it's still a hierarchy of universes, and in fact you can prove those axioms, except for the complication that you have asked <code>Univ</code> to live in a low universe so the definition needs to be divided up by universe level:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Univ0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Sort</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">True</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">univ0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Univ0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">trivial</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Univ1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Sort</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Sort</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">u</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">univ1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Univ1</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">True</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">univ2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Univ1</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Sort</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">u</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">type_in_type0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Univ0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≍</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">univ1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">type_in_type2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Univ1</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≍</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">univ2</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 526216557,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1751130688
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This is the reason why <code>Girard.lean</code> instead deals with a type in the universe which is <code>Equiv</code> to the universe it lives in, because you can have an <code>Equiv</code> between types at different universe levels, but <code>HEq</code> requires both types be at the same level</p>",
        "id": 526216655,
